# Error Handling

**📚 Complete Guide**: `docs/conventions/patterns/error-handling.md`

## Critical Rules

- **Always use `OneJsError`** from `@OneJs/core` — never `new Error()`
- **Always include an `ErrorCode`** from `ErrorCodes` enum
- **Never expose infrastructure errors** to the domain layer

## Import

```typescript
import { OneJsError, ErrorCodes } from '@OneJs/core'
```

## OneJsError Signature

```typescript
new OneJsError(type: string, statusCode: number, message: string, details: object, errorCode: ErrorCodes)
```

## Common Patterns

```typescript
// Validation
throw new OneJsError('Validation failed', 400, 'Password too short', {}, ErrorCodes.VALIDATION_FAILED)

// Not found
throw new OneJsError('Not Found', 404, `User not found: ${id}`, {}, ErrorCodes.USER_NOT_FOUND)

// Conflict / duplicate
throw new OneJsError('Conflict', 409, 'Email already in use', {}, ErrorCodes.USER_ALREADY_EXISTS)

// Unauthorized
throw new OneJsError('Unauthorized', 401, 'Invalid credentials', {}, ErrorCodes.AUTH_INVALID)

// Bad request / expired token
throw new OneJsError('Bad Request', 400, 'Invalid or expired reset token', {}, ErrorCodes.AUTH_INVALID)
```

## Status Code Reference

| Situation | Status | Type |
|---|---|---|
| Invalid input / format | 400 | `'Validation failed'` |
| Invalid/expired token | 400 | `'Bad Request'` |
| Missing/invalid auth | 401 | `'Unauthorized'` |
| Insufficient permissions | 403 | `'Forbidden'` |
| Resource not found | 404 | `'Not Found'` |
| Duplicate resource | 409 | `'Conflict'` |

## Domain-Specific Error Codes

Extend `ErrorCodes` for bounded-context-specific codes. Follow the pattern in `.oneJs/core/src/` for registration.
